//! 
//! This exercise combines these two features to demonstrate the enhancements to Rust's compile-time computing power.
//! 
//! ## Requirements
//! 
//! - Use `const {}` blocks for compile-time evaluation in type locations and runtime contexts
//! - Use `&raw const` in `const fn` to get raw pointer
//! - Understand the safety boundaries of unsafe operations in const contexts

