//! # Unsafe Rust 练习\n//!\n//! 本模块包含 11:
//! #UnsafeRust Exercise
//! 
//! This module contains 11 exercises covering the core concepts of unsafe code in Rust:
//! 
//! | Number | Topic | Difficulty | Test Points |
//! |------|------|------|------|
//! | ex01 | Raw pointers and safe array splitting | Medium | `*mut T`, pointer offsets, borrow checker interaction |
//! | ex02 | FFI boundary safe packaging | Medium | `extern "C"`, C string conversion, safe packaging |
//! | ex03 | MaybeUninit and avoiding unnecessary initialization | Medium | `MaybeUninit<T>`, assuming initialization, Drop safety |
//! | ex04 | UnsafeCell and internal mutability | Medium | `UnsafeCell<T>`, internal mutability, `*const`/`*mut` |
//! | ex05 | Miri verification and undefined behavior identification | Hard | Miri tools, Tree Borrows, UB identification and repair |
//! | ex06 | `mem::transmute` and type pun | Medium | `transmute`, `transmute_copy`, union, alignment constraints |
//! | ex07 | Memory aligned and unaligned access | Hard | `read_unaligned`, `write_unaligned`, `#[repr(packed)]`, `align_offset` |
//! | ex08 | Raw reference operators `&raw const`/`&raw mut` | Medium | `&raw const`, avoid intermediate references UB, packed/union safe access (Rust 1.95) |
//! | ex09 | `unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn` spec | Medium | Rust 2024 unsafe fn semantics, `unsafe {}` granular control (Rust 1.95) |
//! | ex10 | `c"..."` C string literals | Easy | `CStr`, FFI bounds safety, compile-time NUL guarantees (Rust 1.95) |
//! | ex11 | `const {}` blocks and const raw pointers | Hard | `const {}` blocks, `&raw const` in const fn, compile-time evaluation (Rust 1.95) |
//! 
//! ## Run the test
//! 
//! ```bash
//! cd exercises
//! cargo test unsafe_rust::
//! ```
//! 
//! ## Miri verification (needs nightly)
//! 
//! ```bash
//! rustup run nightly cargo miri test unsafe_rust::ex05_miri_validation
//! rustup run nightly cargo miri test unsafe_rust::ex07_align_offset
//! ```

